#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:5
msgid "working as designed"
msgstr "working as designed"

#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:9
msgid "[IBM]"
msgstr "[IBM]"

#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:12
msgid ""
"In conformance to a wrong or inappropriate specification; useful, but "
"misdesigned."
msgstr "誤ったまたは不適切な仕様に準拠していること。役には立つが、設計を誤っている。"

#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:15
msgid "Frequently used as a sardonic comment on a program's utility."
msgstr "プログラムの有用性に対する皮肉なコメントとしてよく使われる。"

#: ../../W/working-as-designed.rst:18
msgid ""
"Unfortunately also used as a bogus reason for not accepting a criticism or "
"suggestion. At :ref:`IBM`\\, this sense is used in official documents! See "
":ref:`BAD`\\."
msgstr ""
"あいにく、批判や提案を受け入れない偽の理由としても使われる。\\ :ref:`IBM`\\ では、この語義は公式文書で使われている! \\ "
":ref:`BAD`\\ を参照。"
